INSERT INTO Users_question VALUES(11,'{"The inhibitor decreases the enzyme''s catalytic efficiency by 50%."}','{"The inhibitor increases the enzyme''s catalytic efficiency by 100%."}','{"The inhibitor has no effect on the enzyme''s catalytic efficiency because Vmax remains constant."}','{"The inhibitor decreases the enzyme''s catalytic efficiency by 10%."}','{"This is the correct answer. Catalytic efficiency is represented by the ratio Vmax/Km. Without the inhibitor, catalytic efficiency is 100/10 = 10. With the inhibitor, it''s 100/20 = 5.  The efficiency is halved (decreased by 50%). This option correctly calculates and interprets the change in catalytic efficiency based on the provided data."}','{''This is incorrect. The Km value increased in the presence of the inhibitor, indicating a lower affinity of the enzyme for the substrate, which would reduce catalytic efficiency, not increase it. Some test takers may confuse the increase in Km with an increase in efficiency. Competitive inhibitors increase Km, which is inversely related to catalytic efficiency.''}','{''This is incorrect. While Vmax does remain constant in the presence of a competitive inhibitor, catalytic efficiency is defined by the ratio of Vmax to Km. Since Km changes, the catalytic efficiency does indeed change. This option ignores the effect of Km on catalytic efficiency, only focusing on Vmax.''}','{''This is incorrect. While the Km increased by a factor of two, the catalytic efficiency is calculated based on the ratio of Vmax to Km. A 10% decrease does not align with the given data. A common mistake is to focus solely on the change in Km, but without using it to correctly compute the ratio of Vmax and Km.''}',1,2,replace('A researcher is studying the effect of a novel competitive inhibitor on the enzyme kinetics of an important metabolic enzyme. They perform Michaelis-Menten kinetics experiments both in the presence and absence of the inhibitor. The following data is obtained:\n\n| Condition             | Vmax (µmol/min) | Km (µM) |\n|-----------------------|-----------------|---------|\n| No Inhibitor          | 100             | 10      |\n| With Inhibitor        | 100             | 20      |\n\nBased on this data, what is the best conclusion about the inhibitor''s effect on the enzyme''s catalytic efficiency?\n','\n',char(10)));
